Our general open source software contribution <a href=https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/komodo/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md>guidelines</a> apply whenever joining or opening improvement proposal discussions.
This repository aims to provide a structured and organized process for discussing and proposing dPoW and notary node operations related improvements. All DIPs should be open to public discussion and revision before they can be reviewed & accepted.

Therefor we ask you to check the roadmaps and issue tickets in the <a href=https://github.com/komodoplatform/dPoW/issues>dPoW repository</a> prior to opening the relevant discussion in the Komodo <a href="https://discord.com/channels/412898016371015680/1132321808268402790">DIPs discord channel</a>.
Furthermore please open a issue ticket in this repository after you confirm your proposal is not redundant / a duplicate.

Please read and ensure you understood the <a href=https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/komodo/blob/master/code_of_conduct.md> Contributor Code of Conduct </a>. By participating in this project, you agree to abide by its terms.
